            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "St. John’s International Residential School – A Nightmare for Students\n\nSt. John’s International Residential School markets itself as a prestigious institution, but the reality behind its walls is deeply concerning. As someone who has witnessed firsthand the severe mismanagement and neglect, I feel obligated to warn parents and students about the shocking human rights violations, health code breaches, and corruption that plague this school.\n\nHuman Rights Violations\nThe school imposes an oppressive environment where students' basic rights are frequently disregarded. Reports of verbal, emotional, and even physical abuse by staff members are disturbingly common. Instead of fostering a safe and supportive educational space, the administration rules through fear, punishing students excessively for minor infractions. The lack of mental health support, coupled with an overwhelming culture of intimidation, has left many students struggling with anxiety and depression.\n\n### **Severe Health and Sanitation Issues**\nThe hostel conditions are appalling. Dormitories are overcrowded, poorly maintained, and unsanitary, with insufficient ventilation and unhygienic restrooms. The food provided is often stale, lacking proper nutritional value, and in some cases, even infested with insects. Several students have fallen ill due to the substandard meals, yet complaints are either ignored or met with retaliation. There is a blatant disregard for health standards, putting students' well-being at serious risk.\n\n### **Corrupt Management & Lack of Accountability**\nThe school's administration is steeped in corruption, prioritizing financial gains over student welfare. Parents are coerced into paying exorbitant fees under false pretenses, while necessary school improvements are conveniently overlooked. Favoritism is rampant, with certain students receiving privileges while others face discrimination. Instead of addressing concerns, the management actively silences complaints, ensuring that their misdeeds remain hidden from public scrutiny.\n\n### **Final Warning to Parents**\nSending a child to St. John’s International Residential School is a decision that should be reconsidered. No amount of academic reputation can justify the neglect, abuse, and exploitation that students endure here. If you value your child’s safety, mental health, and overall well-being, look elsewhere. There are far better institutions that uphold ethical standards, respect students’ rights, and prioritize a nurturing learning environment.\n\nThis school desperately needs intervention from regulatory authorities, and I urge former students and parents to come forward with their experiences to expose the truth.",
